cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM 

This paper is about biomedical image segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and defending against adversarial attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new method for enhancing feature representations using non-local context encoding, which involves attention mechanisms and modeling spatial dependencies. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the vulnerability of CNN-based models to adversarial attacks, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on two different biomedical image segmentation datasets, which could make it relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
